{
  "texts": [
    "This consideration crystallized in the USA in 2021 when the National School Boards Association was forced to apologize for asking the Department of Justice to investigate parent protestors as \"domestic terrorists\" (Rokita et al., 2021).",
    "Restricting public school \"exit\" options may have a negative, and not a positive, effect on parental \"voice\" in education (Barry, 1974, pp. 86-93).",
    "As Hirschmann (1986, p. 89) himself later admitted, parental voice has no force if there is no alternative to the public school system.",
    "It may be precisely when students are a legitimate flight risk, due to the availability of options such as private schooling, that public school officials tend to be most attentive to the voices of parents.",
    "Moreover, the very act of choosing a private school for your child, and the obligations that come with that privilege, have the potential to empower traditionally disenfranchised populations of parents (Stewart & Wolf, 2014, pp. 111-121)."
  ]
}